        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 1 at 8:31PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 831 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Green Lake, or 9 miles east of McFaddin, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Port Lavaca, Seadrift, McFaddin, Guadalupe, Point Comfort, Alamo
Beach, Dacosta, Bloomington, Magnolia Beach, Long Mott, Placedo,
Green Lake, Tivoli, and Austwell.

This includes US Highway 87 between mile markers 818 and 840.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
